<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="271" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Root inquires whether the imperial edict constitutes a practical
                            nullification of the declaration of 1898 that an Englishman shall be
                            inspector-general.)</p>
